    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_"><text styleclass="Heading3_atocs_" translate="true">Ball-Joint dialog-box</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Usually, you would edit the Ball-Joint at each end of the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Connecting-Part" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Connecting-Part</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:160px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:right;"><image src="Dialog-13.2-BallJoint.ipp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Parameter-Header"><text styleclass="Parameter-Header" translate="true">Ball Diameter</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Edit the diameter of the Ball symbol in </text><text styleclass="Interface" translate="true">graphic-area.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">Note: &#160;</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Do </text><text styleclass="T_Menu" translate="true">Visibility toolbar &gt; </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Visibility-Show-Model-in-Mechanism" styleclass="T_Menu" translate="true">Show Model in Mechanism</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> to view the symbol for the Ball. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Parameter-Header"><text styleclass="Parameter-Header" translate="true">Ball Offset &#160;</text><text styleclass="BodyText BI" translate="true">(±)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Edit the perpendicular distance </text><text styleclass="BodyText BI" translate="true">(±)</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> from the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Plane-Mechanism" styleclass="Element" translate="true">Mechanism Plane</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> to the centre of the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Ball-Joint.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Why do you need the </text><text styleclass="Parameter-Header" translate="true">Ball-Offset</text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true"> parameter?</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text - bit bit bigger2"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Unlike other kinematic-elements, the centre of </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Ball-Joints</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> are frequently </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="color:#ff0000;" translate="true">not</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> on </text><text styleclass="Interface" translate="true">Mechanism-Plane. </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">It is important that the offset distance to the centre of the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Ball-Joint</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> is correct to make sure the kinematic-analysis is correct.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso"><text styleclass="SeeAlso" translate="true">See also : </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Ball-Joint-Configurations" styleclass="SeeAlso" translate="true">Ball-Joint Configurations</link></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Parameter-Header"><text styleclass="Parameter-Header" translate="true">Ball Mass</text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Enter the Mass of the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Ball-Joint</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Its centre-of-mass is coplanar with the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Mechanism-Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">. even if the </text><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Ball-Offset ≠ 0 </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
